Package com.abdcelik

Class FileSystemTree

java.lang.Object
com.abdcelik.FileSystemTree
public class FileSystemTree
extends java.lang.Object
FileSystemTree handle a file system hierarchy in a general tree structure.

  • Method Details

    • addDir

      public void addDir​(java.lang.String path)
      Adds new directory to the system. Starter addDir method. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      path - the path of the new directory

    • addFile

      public void addFile​(java.lang.String path)
      Adds new file to the system. Starter addFile method. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      path - the path of the new file

    • add

      private void add​(FileSystemTree.FileNode node, java.lang.String[] paths, int index, FileSystemTree.FileNode.State state)
      Adds new directory or file to the system recursively. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      node - current node
      paths - paths array of the new directory or file
      index - paths array's index to direct paths array
      state - new node's state. State can be DIRECTORY OR FILE

    • remove

      public void remove​(java.lang.String path)
      Removes a directory or file from the system. Starter remove method. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      path - the path of the removed directory or file

    • remove

      private void remove​(FileSystemTree.FileNode node, java.lang.String[] paths, int index)
      Removes a directory or file from the system recursively. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      node - current node
      paths - path array of the removed directory or file
      index - paths array's index to direct paths array

    • search

      public void search​(java.lang.String searched)
      Searches the entire file system for a directory or a file including the given search characters in its name. Starter search method. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      searched - the search characters

    • search

      private void search​(FileSystemTree.FileNode node, java.lang.String searched, java.lang.StringBuilder sb)
      Searches the entire file system for a directory or a file including the given search characters in its name recursively. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      node - current node
      searched - the search characters
      sb - StringBuilder instance for appending path for each recursion call and if searched character is founded, path will be printed

    • printFileSystem

      public void printFileSystem()
      Prints the file system. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm. This method calls toString method.

    • toString

      public java.lang.String toString()
      Returns string representation of the file system. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.

    • toString

      private void toString​(FileSystemTree.FileNode node, int depth, java.lang.StringBuilder sb)
      Returns string representation of the file system recursively. Method use pre-order(root - left subtree - right subtree) traversal algorithm.
      Parameters:
      node - current node
      depth - current node's depth
